<div class='description'><p>I&#39;m a community activist who has been hacking with ruby since 2005, and look forward to finding new ways to make software useful to the world, together.</p>
<p>When I heard about Greg&#39;s idea for Ruby Mendicant U., I was devouring his <em><a href="http://rubybestpractices.com/">Ruby Best Practices</a></em> book, chapter by chapter. The idea sounded like an active extension of that book, with its unique emphasis on teaching software design through diving into real-world code, so how could it not be great? I took the first course in September 2010 and have been actively involved in the alumni network since, watching us grow into a community far beyond what Greg or any of us could have imagined.</p>
<p>At MU, I coordinate the one-on-one <a href="https://github.com/mendicant-university/mentoring">mentoring program</a> and help to develop MU&#39;s broader social mission, including organizing the <a href="http://projects.mendicantuniversity.org/">Hackfest for Great Justice</a> in October. I was part of the team that built the <a href="http://www.swan4kids.org/">website for SWAN</a>. I joined the MU staff in September.</p>
